main event: An object found in Gary, Minnesota was submitted for analysis, believed to be a possible 'false star'.
interesting points: The object was found in the yard of a resident who had lived in the area for 3 years, around the time the Russian Sputnik pieces were found in Wisconsin.
The resident sent a sample of the object to the Air Force for identification and analysis.
The analysis concluded that the samples were consistent with common materials and did not contain any unusual or significant constituents.
The report recommended continuing the investigation and adding it to the investigative file.
The report indicates the object was sent to the Air Force's Project Blue Book program, which investigated unidentified flying objects.
sighted object: an unidentified object found in a resident's yard
photographs: no, the report does not include any photographs
